@startuml
' @id(SEQ-RENDER-DIFF-SVG)
' @ref(USE-DIFF-DIAGRAM)
'
' Objective-side flow for rasterizing a cycle's superposed .diff.puml
' files to SVG so the viewer (which has no PlantUML engine) can paint
' them. Triggered by /mdd-cycle's close step and by /mdd-render.
'
' @desc(SEQ-RENDER-DIFF-SVG, "How each .mdd/cycles/<n>/<kind>/<name>.diff.puml is rasterized to .mdd/rendered/cycles/<n>/<kind>/<name>.diff.svg by the cycle-close step and /mdd-render, keeping the rendered path a deterministic mirror of the source path.")
title Rasterize cycle diff pumls to SVG (objective)

actor "Developer" as Dev
participant "/mdd-cycle close\nor /mdd-render" as Trigger
participant "DiffRenderer\n(mdd-render)" as Rend
database ".mdd/cycles/<n>/\n<kind>/<name>.diff.puml" as Store
participant "PlantUML jar\n(+ Graphviz dot)" as PUML
database ".mdd/rendered/cycles/<n>/\n<kind>/<name>.diff.svg" as Out

Dev -> Trigger : close cycle N (or /mdd-render)
Trigger -> Store : enumerate **/*.diff.puml under cycle N
loop each <kind>/<name>.diff.puml
  Trigger -> Rend : render(source = cycles/N/<kind>/<name>.diff.puml)
  Rend -> Rend : derive out = rendered/cycles/N/<kind>/<name>.diff.svg
  Rend -> PUML : plantuml -tsvg < diff.puml
  alt render ok
    PUML --> Rend : svg
    Rend -> Out : write deterministic mirror path
  else dot/syntax diagnostic
    PUML --> Rend : diagnostic text
    Rend -> Trigger : report readiness warning (non-blocking)
  end
end
Trigger --> Dev : cycle N closed; diff SVGs available to the viewer

note over Out
  Path is a pure mirror: cycles/<n>/<rel>.diff.puml
  -> rendered/cycles/<n>/<rel>.diff.svg
  (OCL-DIFF-SVG-PATH-DERIVED). The viewer never
  invokes PlantUML; it only consumes this SVG.
end note
@enduml
